Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  Malaysiaâ€™s  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 0.7 percent
to 1,437.61. The market will be shut tomorrow for a holiday.  Glomac Bhd. (GLMC)  : The Malaysian property developer
said its Thai unit agreed to sell its 49 percent stake in WHA
Glomac Alliance Co. for 30.9 million ringgit ($10 million),
according to a company statement. Glomac dropped 2 percent to
1.49 ringgit.  Malaysian Airline System Bhd. (MAS)  : The national
carrier said it appointed Ahmad Jauhari Yahya managing director.
The appointment will take effect on Sept. 19, the company said
in an exchange filing. Jauhari had previously been managing
director at Malakoff Bhd., Malaysian Resources Corp. Bhd. and
Time Engineering Bhd., the company said. The stock fell 0.7
percent to 1.44 ringgit.        Notion VTEC Bhd. (NVB)  : The metal processor and tools
manufacturer said it plans to sell its 70 percent stake in Swiss
Impression Sdn., a maker of tools and parts used for digital
cameras and other consumer electronic devices. Notion retreated
1.7 percent to 1.70 ringgit.  PLB Engineering Bhd. (PLB)  : The builder and property
group agreed to buy land for 18 million ringgit from closely
held Majestic Heights Sdn., it said in a statement. PLB last
traded at 86.5 sen on Sept. 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
